text:
Met with a rude service attitude by their staff with long black hair tied in a ponytail. When I brought my own flask and told her to put the coffee in there, she raised her voice and asked me to repeat my order 3 times.
Even my mum asked me if it was the same lady with a bad temper.
The taste of the coffee is greatly influenced by the temperament of the one who pours the coffee. And my coffee tasted bitter this morning.
I hope that Teck Huat management will teach her anger management.
Very nice and thick kopi O gosong, my husband loves to buy their Roti. Will take picture next visit. Small cup $1. Not bad lah üëçü§≠
There was a long queue on a Saturday morning, but the coffee was good.
This is one the few coffee stalls that serves both strong coffee and tea. The toast bread is also very popular.
Their butter slab doesn‚Äôt go all the way through, they only put small pieces at the cuts. Still delicious though!
